For years, a mysterious phenomenon in research has caused uncertainty: Dark matter influences the speed of space probes during so-called swing-by manoeuvres.
Experts fear that Albert Einstein's general theory of relativity could not be entirely correct.
For almost 18 years, the "Ulysses" spacecraft flew through space.
