The motorists, who can be held back because of the alcohol level, will have to install the `Alcolock'.
The Authority has ordered that the driver who had three official penalties for the alcohol level install in his car this system, which prohibits him from starting the car in a drunk state. If he is alcoholic, the car does not jump.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the Public Prosecutor’s report. According to them, it is a pilot project that will last for one year.
The aim is to re-socialize the driver, which is why he is getting a course for re-education of traffic behaviour.
The Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for Motor Vehicle Safety will also participate in it, in addition to the public prosecutorate-general's experience.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of motorists who were more than once exposed to alcohol because of driving returned to control.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the breathed air and prevents autostart if the driver has done alcohol tests; or if a concentration of alcohol is found which is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by those who impose the penalty.
In this context, a study carried out in the US in 2007 showed that cars equipped with these devices already in the first year after its introduction prevent up to 65% of the standard infringements.
In Spain, 115 lives can be saved annually.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behaviour before it became a criminal offence.
And in order to facilitate its implementation, legislative reform can be carried out on the usual basis, yet a reform of the basic law is called for, which is necessary for the prosecution process.
The device is still available on the Spanish markets, not in any store, although it has already been installed in some commercial vehicles and public transport vehicles.
Only tomorrow will the House of Representatives vote because of the initiative of the Spanish Socialist Workers' Party, which proposes to install this system in school buses. This has already been done in France.
