Grapefruit juice was already suspected of being responsible for increasing the effects of some medicines such as antibiotics, antiasthmatics, cardiovascular medications, anxiolytic and neurological agents, up to toxic levels.
MEDICINAL PRODUCTS – The same Agency of the medicine had warned doctors and patients about the dangers of this mixture in a report two years ago, and stressed that attention should be paid to what is drunk in combination with medicines such as diazepan or methadone.
IT IS NOT GRAPH FRUIT – According to the experts, orange juice and apple juice also contain substances that can inhibit the medicines.
The list of active substances inhibited by fruit juices is long.
Therefore the appeal of Michele Carruba, Director of the Università Statale di Milano: "Such results are usually forwarded immediately to the various international manufacturers who are free to change the consumer information.
